The House Committee on Judiciary, Non-Civil offers the following substitute to HB 430:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 1 of Title 42 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to Sexual Offender Risk Review Board, so as to provide for venue for certain
3 petitions regarding the state sexual offender registry; to provide for related matters; to repeal
4 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 2 of Chapter 1 of Title 42 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 Sexual Offender Risk Review Board, is amended by revising paragraph (6) of subsection (e)
9 of Code Section 42-1-12, relating to State Sexual Offender Registry, as follows:
10 "(6) Is a nonresident who changes residence from another state or territory of the United
11 States or any other place to Georgia who, at the time of changing residence, is required
12 to register as a sexual offender under federal law, military law, tribal law, or the laws of
13 another state or territory or who has been convicted in this state of a criminal offense
14 against a victim who is a minor or any dangerous sexual offense;"
